<header> 
	<h1> Leading Change </h1>
	  <img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2521/4223670815_79b7fc343b.jpg"
	  </header>
	
	<p>As manager's it is our expectation to champion change. We have several tools on how to manage through change. The tools we have are effective in helping us understanding what is happening during the acceptance of a change. </p>

	<h1> We are in a constently changing environment. </h1>
	<p> Maintaining a positive working environment amonst the change is changing.</p>

	<p> There is a need for a new perspective. A well planned, consistent approach to moving an idea into a lasting action. </p>

	<h2> John Kotter created the 8 steps of leading change.</h2>
	<or>
	<li> Establish a sense of urgency.
		Why is the change nessecary?
		There is no room for complacency in successsful organizations
		</li>

	<li> Build and Maintain a guiding Coalition
		Who are the drivers for the change? Who sponsors the project?
		This applies to large and small projects.
</li>

<li> Formulate a strategic vision, create a plan of action and a brief description of the desired result.
		Keep in mind each change has it's own result.
</li>

<li> Communicate broadly from various channels. 
		Be transparent, share the vision 
</li>

	<li> Empower broad based action
		Identify and remove obsticles
		Encourage non traditional ideas,activities, and actions.
</li>

	<li> Generate Short Term Wins
		Create the Wins then recognize and reward the people who made the wins possible.
</li>

	<li> Never Let up, Don't declare victory too soon.
		Change takes endurance.
</li>

	<li>Anchor change to the culture.
		Align the change to the culture, the broader vision.
</li>
</or>
<h3>Imagine feeling prepared and supported to lead change by inspiring others with a clear vision of the end result. </h3>

